	* mate-settings-daemon/main.c: (main):
	Add missing files.  Add some more profiling points.

2008-03-24  William Jon McCann  <jmccann@redhat.com>

	* configure.ac:
	* mate-settings-daemon/Makefile.am:
	* mate-settings-daemon/mate-settings-manager.c: (_load_file),
	(_load_dir), (_load_all), (mate_settings_manager_start):
	* mate-settings-daemon/mate-settings-plugin-info.c:
	(mate_settings_plugin_info_fill_from_file), (load_plugin_module),
	(_activate_plugin):
	* mate-settings-daemon/main.c: (bus_register), (main):
	Add some profiling code.  Must specify --enable-profiling to
	configure.

	Can now be profiled like so:
	strace -ttt -f -o /tmp/logfile.strace mate-settings-daemon
	python plot-timeline.py -o prettygraph.png /tmp/logfile.strace

	See: http://www.mate.org/~federico/news-2006-03.html#09

2008-03-24  Jens Granseuer  <jensgr@gmx.net>

	Patch by: Alexey Shabalin <a.shabalin@gmail.com>

	* plugins/sound/gsd-sound-manager.c: (apply_settings): now that
	"starting esd" can mean either esd or PulseAudio, check the MateConf
	setting for starting the sound server even when esd is disabled
	(bug #523743)

